{
  "doc_id": "3033",
  "text": "Phenotypes Using Cluster Analyses. In recent years, several studies have used cluster analyses to examine cohorts of COPD patients aiming at the identification of clinical phenotypes in stable patients [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] [CITATION_9] . In the present paper, we will not examine studies performed in mixed populations of patients with various chronic airway diseases [CITATION_10] [CITATION_11] , in COPD patients recruited in clinical trials [CITATION_12] (i.e., who may not be representative of the real-world COPD population), nor studies that aimed at the identification of phenotypes of COPD exacerbations [CITATION_13] .",
